    <div class="health-info-wrapper">
      <div class="health-info-container">
        <div class="health-card"><img src="images/healthinfo1.png" /><div class="image-line"></div><h3>Stay Healthy! Stay Strong!</h3><p>A health awareness that highlights three main tips: eating nutritious food (fruits, vegetables, whole grains, and limiting sugar), exercising regularly (at least 30 minutes of activity), and managing stress (relaxation, enough sleep, and talking to others). The poster includes images of healthy food, people exercising, stress management, and sleep.</p></div>
        <div class="health-card"><img src="images/healthinfo2.png" /><div class="image-line"></div><h3>Wash your Hands!</h3><p>Proper handwashing in four simple steps to prevent germs and illnesses. It shows how to start by wetting hands with clean water, then applying soap and scrubbing for at least 20 seconds. Next, it reminds people to scrub all surfaces of the hands and finally rinse them thoroughly with water. The colorful illustrations of children, hands, soap, and water make the instructions easy to understand and follow, especially for students and young learners.</p></div>
        <div class="health-card"><img src="images/healthinfo3.png" /><div class="image-line"></div><h3>Health Matters</h3><p>Health is one of the most valuable aspects of our lives, as it affects how we think, feel, and perform every day. Taking care of our body and mind through proper nutrition, regular exercise, and stress management helps us stay strong and prevent diseases. Good health also means maintaining personal hygiene, like washing hands properly, to avoid infections and keep our surroundings safe. When we prioritize health, we not only improve our own well-being but also contribute to a healthier and happier community. Truly, health matters because it is the foundation of living a balanced and fulfilling life.</p></div>
        <div class="health-card"><img src="images/healthinfo4.png" /><div class="image-line"></div><h3>LET US HELP YOU TAKE CARE OF YOUR HEALTH</h3><p>Taking care of your health doesn’t have to be difficult—you just need the right guidance and support. With simple steps like eating well, exercising regularly, managing stress, and practicing good hygiene, you can stay strong and prevent illness. We are here to remind you that small healthy choices every day make a big difference. Together, let’s build a healthier, happier you.</p></div>
        <div class="health-card"><img src="images/healthinfo5.png" /><div class="image-line"></div><h3>FIVE WAYS TO FIGHT THE FLU</h3><p>Protect yourself and others by following five simple steps to fight the flu. First, practice proper handwashing to stop the spread of germs. Second, eat a balanced diet and stay hydrated to keep your immune system strong. Third, get enough rest and regular exercise to maintain your body’s defenses. Fourth, cover your mouth and nose when coughing or sneezing to prevent infecting others. Finally, consider getting a flu vaccine for added protection. Small actions every day can go a long way in keeping you healthy during flu season.</p></div>
